<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>Dashboard</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Julius+Sans+One&family=Just+Me+Again+Down+Here&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=MedievalSharp&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Michroma&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/dashc.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="navigationWrapper">
        <div class="logoWrapper">
          <span class="stylish">KRAC</span>
          <span class="logo">IT</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="navigation">
          <!-- Avatar Profile Menu -->
          <li class="parent profile-menu">
            <div class="avatar" id="profileAvatar"></div>
            <div class="profile-dropdown" id="profileDropdown">
              <button class="signout-btn">Sign Out</button>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

  <!--first page-->
  <section class="cv-analyzer">
    <div class="cv-content">
      <h2>CV analyzer</h2>
      <p>
        The Resume/CV Analysis feature allows,<br>
        users to upload their resumes, which are<br>
        then scanned by AI to evaluate content,<br>
        structure, and relevance. It identifies<br>
        strengths like clear formatting or relevant<br>
        skills, while also pointing out weak areas<br>
        such as missing keywords, vague<br>
        descriptions, or formatting issues. Users<br>
        receive tailored suggestions to improve<br>
        their resumes, along with an overall score<br>
        indicating how well their resume aligns with<br>
        job expectations. This helps users create<br>
        stronger, more job-ready resumes with<br>
        clear, actionable feedback.
      </p>
      <button class="analyze-btn" onclick="window.open('https://huggingface.co/spaces/somil402/resumaanalyzer', '_blank')">Analyze your CV</button>

    </div>
    <div class="cv-image">
      <img src="images/cvimg.jpg" alt="CV Illustration">
    </div>
  </section>
  


  <!--page 2-->
  <section class="job-preparation">
    <div class="job-prep-content">
      <h2>The Job Preparation</h2>
      <p>
        The Job Preparation Resources feature provides users with a curated set of
        materials to help them get ready for the placement process. This includes
        resume writing tips, commonly asked interview questions, sample answers,
        coding practice platforms, soft skills development guides, and
        company-specific preparation strategies. The resources are tailored to the
        user's career goals and updated regularly to match industry trends, helping
        them build confidence and improve their chances of success in interviews
        and assessments.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="job-prep-buttons">
      <button class="prep-button">Aptitude Question</button>
      <button class="prep-button">Coding question</button>
      <button class="prep-button">Interview question</button>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!--page 3 -->
  <section class="aptitude-test">
    <div class="aptitude-content">
      <h2>Check your knowledge</h2>
      <p>
        The Aptitude Tests feature evaluates a user's general aptitude through a series
        of quizzes and tasks. These tests are tailored to the user's chosen field or job
        role and cover topics like logical reasoning, problem-solving, communication, and
        more. After completion, users receive instant results, including a performance
        score, strengths, and areas for improvement. This helps to prepare better for
        real job opportunities.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="aptitude-button">
      <button class="assessment-button">Take Assessment</button>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!--4th page -->
  <section class="interview-simulation">
    <div class="interview-content">
      <h2>INTERVIEW SIMULATION</h2>
      <p>
        The AI Interview Simulation feature lets users practice interviews in a realistic,
        AI-driven environment. Users respond to a set of questions through text or voice,
        and the AI analyzes their answers to evaluate communication skills, clarity of
        thought, and content quality. After the session, users receive feedback
        highlighting strengths, weak areas, and suggestions for improvement. This helps
        them build confidence, refine their answers, and prepare effectively for real interviews.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="interview-button">
      <button class="practice-button">Practice the interview</button>
    </div>
  </section>
      
      
      


   <script src="js/dashj.js"></script> 
</body>
</html>